    "summary": "Agree, one reservation about \"poeticality\"",
    "content": "Yes, still agree with \"the poetic\" / \"the Poetic\" / \"poetic\" as adjective.\n\nOne reservation: \"poeticality\" is clunky. In English it sounds like a back-formation that draws attention to itself as a word rather than pointing through to the concept. If a noun form is occasionally needed beyond \"the poetic,\" I would prefer \"poetic stance\" or \"poetic mode\" over \"poeticality.\" But this is minor -- if the translator finds a sentence where \"poeticality\" is the only grammatically clean option, it is acceptable. Just not as a routine variant."
  }
